abstract: The United States will host a conference in about a month on 5G that U.S. President Donald Trump will attend and that will include companies such as Samsung Electronics Co Ltd, National Economic Council Director Larry Kudlow told reporters on Friday.
snippet: The United States will host a conference in about a month on 5G that U.S. President Donald Trump will attend and that will include companies such as Samsung Electronics Co Ltd, National Economic Council Director Larry Kudlow told reporters on Frid...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The United States will host a conference in about a month on 5G that U.S. President Donald Trump will attend and that will include companies such as Samsung Electronics Co Ltd, National Economic Council Director Larry Kudlow told reporters on Friday.
headline_main: U.S. Will Host 5G Conference Including Companies in About a Month: Kudlow
headline_print_headline: U.S. Will Host 5G Conference Including Companies in About a Month: Kudlow

abstract: U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo met Friday with the new ruler of Oman, a Gulf Arab country that has close ties with both Washington and Tehran and that has previously provided a back channel for talks between the adversaries.
snippet: U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo met Friday with the new ruler of Oman, a Gulf Arab country that has close ties with both Washington and Tehran and that has previously provided a back channel for talks between the adversaries.
lead_paragraph: DUBAI, United Arab Emirates — U.S. Secretary of State Mike Pompeo met Friday with the new ruler of Oman, a Gulf Arab country that has close ties with both Washington and Tehran and that has previously provided a back channel for talks between the adversaries.
headline_main: Pompeo Meets With Oman's New Ruler Amid US Pressure on Iran
headline_print_headline: Pompeo Meets With Oman's New Ruler Amid US Pressure on Iran

abstract: President Donald Trump said on Friday he had four candidates under consideration to be the next U.S. intelligence chief and that a decision would be made soon, even as one potential candidate said he was not interested in the job.
snippet: President Donald Trump said on Friday he had four candidates under consideration to be the next U.S. intelligence chief and that a decision would be made soon, even as one potential candidate said he was not interested in the job.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Donald Trump said on Friday he had four candidates under consideration to be the next U.S. intelligence chief and that a decision would be made soon, even as one potential candidate said he was not interested in the job.
headline_main: Trump Says He Is Eyeing Four Candidates for Intelligence Chief
headline_print_headline: Trump Says He Is Eyeing Four Candidates for Intelligence Chief

abstract: Democratic voters feel generally positive about all of their top candidates running for president, but they have only moderate confidence that their party’s nomination process is fair, according to a new poll by The Associated Press-NORC Center for Public Affairs Research.
snippet: Democratic voters feel generally positive about all of their top candidates running for president, but they have only moderate confidence that their party’s nomination process is fair, according to a new poll by The Associated Press-NORC Center fo...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democratic voters feel generally positive about all of their top candidates running for president, but they have only moderate confidence that their party’s nomination process is fair, according to a new poll by The Associated Press-NORC Center for Public Affairs Research.
headline_main: AP-NORC Poll: Democrats Feel Mixed About Nomination Process
headline_print_headline: AP-NORC Poll: Democrats Feel Mixed About Nomination Process

abstract: A temporary truce between the United States and the Taliban took effect on Friday, setting the stage for the two sides to sign a peace deal next week aimed at ending 18 years of war in Afghanistan and bringing U.S. troops home.
snippet: A temporary truce between the United States and the Taliban took effect on Friday, setting the stage for the two sides to sign a peace deal next week aimed at ending 18 years of war in Afghanistan and bringing U.S. troops home.
lead_paragraph: ISLAMABAD — A temporary truce between the United States and the Taliban took effect on Friday, setting the stage for the two sides to sign a peace deal next week aimed at ending 18 years of war in Afghanistan and bringing U.S. troops home.
headline_main: US, Taliban Truce Takes Effect, Setting Stage for Peace Deal
headline_print_headline: US, Taliban Truce Takes Effect, Setting Stage for Peace Deal

abstract: The bank’s $13 billion purchase of E-Trade is expected to inspire more mergers among asset managers.
